Filter the solution into a glass beaker for crystallization. Cover the beaker with a porous preservative film and allow the filtrate to slowly evaporate at room temperature. After about 2−3 weeks, obtain block or prismatic crystals suitable for X-ray analysis.

synthesis.procedure: Mix Tb4O7 (0.093g, 0.125mmol), AgNO3 (0.043g, 0.25mmol), pyridine-2,3-dicarboxylic acid (0.167g, 1.0mmol), H2C2O4·2H2O (0.063g, 0.5mmol), and water (14mL).
